<subSubSection pageId="63" pageNumber="64" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="63.[189,1399,849,985]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<bibRefCitation author="Aellen" box="[189,394,849,875]" firstAuthor="Aellen" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="69 - 71" refId="ref255196" refString="Aellen V. 1966. Addenda. In: Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. The Bats of the Congo and Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen (8) 154: 69 - 71." type="journal article" year="1966">Aellen (1966: 71</bibRefCitation>
, map 98) reported six specimens from Elisabethville (= Lubumbashi) and Jadotville (= Likasi) in southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[508,572,886,912]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">DRC</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman &amp; Hill" box="[586,909,885,912]" firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" refId="ref265812" refString="Hayman R. W. &amp; Hill J. E. 1971. Order Chiroptera. In: Meester J. &amp; Setzer H. W. (eds) The Mammals of Africa, an Identification Manual. Part 2. Smithsonian Institution Press, Washington." type="book" year="1971">Hayman &amp; Hill (1971: 60)</bibRefCitation>
considered 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Eric Hill" authorityYear="1937" box="[1057,1189,885,911]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chitauensis">
<emphasis box="[1057,1189,885,911]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">chitauensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cabrera &amp; Ruxton" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[189,319,923,948]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niveiventer">
<emphasis box="[189,319,923,948]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">niveiventer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which was followed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koopman" box="[618,883,922,949]" firstAuthor="Koopman" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="353 - 444" refId="ref268702" refString="Koopman K. F. 1975. Bats of the Sudan. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History 154 (4): 353 - 444. Available from http: // hdl. handle. net / 2246 / 609 [accessed 29 Nov. 2017]." type="journal article" year="1975">Koopman (1975: 421)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Freeman" box="[895,1144,922,949]" firstAuthor="Freeman" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref261980" refString="Freeman P. W. 1981. A multivariate study of the family Molossidae (Mammalia, Chiroptera): morphology, ecology, evolution. Fieldiana Zoology N. S. 7: 1 - 173. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 3128" type="book chapter" year="1981">Freeman (1981: 160)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Simmons" firstAuthor="Simmons" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="312 - 567" refId="ref273235" refString="Simmons N. B. 2005. Order Chiroptera. In: Wilson D. E. &amp; Reeder D. M. (eds) Mammal Species of the World: A Taxonomic and Geographic Reference: 312 - 567. The John Hopkins University Press, Baltimore." type="book chapter" year="2005">Simmons (2005: 443)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[189,1398,1023,1233]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<bibRefCitation author="Hayman" box="[189,508,1023,1050]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Hayman" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="1 - 105" refId="ref265860" refString="Hayman R. W., Misonne X. &amp; Verheyen W. N. 1966. The bats of the Congo and of Rwanda and Burundi. Annalen van het Koninklijk Museum voor Midden Afrika, Zoologische Wetenschappen, Ser. 8, 154: 1 - 105." type="journal article" year="1966">
Hayman 
<emphasis box="[301,366,1023,1049]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">et al.</emphasis>
(1966: 65)
</bibRefCitation>
did not provide a separate map for this species, but probably included the specimen on the map for 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="A. Smith" baseAuthorityYear="1833" box="[550,882,1060,1086]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="condylura" subGenus="Mops">
<emphasis box="[550,882,1060,1086]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Tadarida (Mops) condylura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(map 99). They reported the species from Astrida (= Butare, 
<collectingCountry box="[412,513,1096,1123]" name="Rwanda" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
), Samba (Maniema Province), a number of localities around Elisabethville (= Lubumbashi) and Jadoville (= Likasi) in Haut-Katanga Province, and from Luluabourg (= Kananga, Kasaï-Central Province). Additional records were found from 
<collectingCountry box="[967,1066,1169,1195]" name="Rwanda" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1085,1184,1169,1195]" name="Burundi" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Burundi</collectingCountry>
, the area around Kananga and the area around Kikwit (Kwilu Province).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="63.[189,1399,1270,1515]" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">
<bibRefCitation author="Cotterill" box="[189,455,1270,1297]" firstAuthor="Cotterill" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" pagination="525 - 526" refId="ref258903" refString="Cotterill F. P. D. 2013 g. Tadarida niveiventer White-bellied Free-tailed Bat. In: Happold M. &amp; Happold D. (eds) Mammals of Africa Volume IV. Hedgehogs, Shrews and Bats: 525 - 526. Bloomsbury Publishing, London." type="book chapter" year="2013" yearSuffix="g">
Cotterill (
<quantity box="[307,386,1270,1296]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="2.013" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" unit="g" value="2013.0">2013g</quantity>
: 526)
</bibRefCitation>
mentioned that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Cabrera &amp; Ruxton" baseAuthorityYear="1926" box="[657,787,1271,1296]" class="Mammalia" family="Molossidae" genus="Tadarida" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="63" pageNumber="64" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="niveiventer">
<emphasis box="[657,787,1271,1296]" italics="true" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">niveiventer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is found in wetter savannas (miombo woodland). On his map, he marked an area covering southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[869,932,1307,1333]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">DRC</collectingCountry>
, western 
<collectingCountry box="[1052,1142,1307,1333]" name="Zambia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and extreme eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[189,275,1343,1369]" name="Angola" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Angola</collectingCountry>
and a second area on the border between 
<collectingCountry box="[767,857,1343,1369]" name="Zambia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and northwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1075,1234,1343,1369]" name="Mozambique" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
. Furthermore, he plotted a number of individual localities in 
<collectingCountry box="[722,821,1380,1406]" name="Rwanda" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
, the 
<collectingCountry box="[874,937,1380,1406]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">DRC</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[948,1038,1380,1406]" name="Zambia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1091,1181,1380,1406]" name="Angola" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Angola</collectingCountry>
. Our map suggests a more uniform distribution from central 
<collectingCountry box="[665,754,1416,1442]" name="Angola" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Angola</collectingCountry>
, the entire territory of 
<collectingCountry box="[1013,1103,1416,1442]" name="Zambia" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Zambia</collectingCountry>
and reaching the western part of 
<collectingCountry box="[275,368,1453,1479]" name="Malawi" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Malawi</collectingCountry>
, and a second area connecting the remaining 
<collectingCountry box="[907,967,1453,1479]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">DRC</collectingCountry>
localities with those in 
<collectingCountry box="[1252,1348,1453,1479]" name="Rwanda" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Rwanda</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[189,289,1489,1515]" name="Burundi" pageId="63" pageNumber="64">Burundi</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
